<chapter><title>Constants</title>
<indexterm><primary>GTK Class</primary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>Classes</primary>
<secondary>GTK</secondary></indexterm>

<para>There are a number of constants available for use with the RexxGTK library. These
are all grouped together as class constants belonging to the GTK class. All of these
constants coorespond to the GTK C header defines and enums. This makes it much easier
to port a C program to ooRexx because you do not have to define them yourself.</para>

<para>Here is an example of how you would use one of these constants.</para>

<programlisting>
<![CDATA[
>>--gtk~gtk_buttons_ok---------------------------------------------------><
]]>
</programlisting>

